All 4 real warnings are pre-existing (in `connection.rs` and `plex.rs`), none from mock_server. All good.

**Summary of what was built:**

**`src/mock_server.rs`** — Mock Groovy UDP server for integration testing:
- Listens on ephemeral port, runs in background thread
- Validates all 6 protocol commands: init (0x02), switchres (0x03), blit (0x07), audio (0x04), close (0x01), get_status (0x05)
- Sends back 13-byte FPGA status ACKs with proper flags (vram_ready, vram_synced)
- Handles multi-packet blit/audio payloads (header + MTU-chunked data)
- Verifies LZ4 decompression on compressed blit payloads
- Records stats: frame counts, byte totals, last init/switchres state, protocol errors
- Thread-safe `MockStats` accessible via `stats()` or `stop()`

**10 tests added** (59 total, all passing):
- `test_mock_init_and_ack` — init packet validation + ACK response
- `test_mock_switchres` — switchres parsing roundtrip
- `test_mock_close` — close command counting
- `test_mock_blit_compressed_lz4` — single compressed blit with LZ4 validation
- `test_mock_audio` — audio header + chunked PCM payload
- `test_mock_unknown_command` — error detection for bad commands
- `test_mock_init_wrong_size` — error detection for malformed packets
- `test_mock_multiple_blits` — 10 sequential blits
- `test_mock_full_session` — complete init→switchres→30 blits→close session
- `test_integration_stream_test_pattern_to_mock` — **streams ~300 frames (~5s at 60fps)** of test pattern, verifies frame count and protocol correctness
